                        <msContents>
                            
                            <summary>Charm relating to the opening of goldmines.</summary>
                            <textLang mainLang="ms">Malay</textLang>
                            
                            <msItem xml:id="Wellcome_Malay_2_Part_2_Item_1">
                                
                                <note>Roman script.</note>
                                
                                <note>This describes the procedure for the opening of a gold mine, including charms which appeal to spirits residing in the natural landscape. 
                                    It also mentions the times when miners are allowed to work – work at mid-day or dusk is not allowed, nor when there is sunshine and rain at the same time. 
                                    The incense burned during the procedure may be used as a divining omen, depending on how the direction in which the smoke rises. </note>
                                
