                        <msContents>
                            
                            <summary>Lovers' prayers and charms for protection when entering the jungle.</summary>
                            
                            <textLang mainLang="ms">Malay</textLang>
                            
                            <msItem xml:id="Wellcome_Malay_2_Part_4_Item_1">
                                
                                <note>Various prayers and charms (doa) for protection against harm, especially against spirits and the natural dangers of the jungle.</note>
                                
                                <note>Roman script.</note>
                                
                                <note>An attached note from <persName>Mohammed Jaafar</persName> explains that the information was obtained from
                                    <persName>Batin Dotai</persName>. The note is dated <date>21 January 1886</date>. 
                                    In all correspondence, Jaafar addresses his letter to "Yang dihormat Tuan" a formal addressed meaning "Respected sir/master".</note>
                                
                                <note>There is also an English glossary of various Malay terms and titles by <persName>G. D. Rauffer [?]</persName>, dated <date>1900</date>.</note>
                                
